headline.print_headline: Wholesale Inventories Showed Rise in January

snippet: The increase reported by the Commerce Department suggests that an overhang in wholesale stocks could persist and hold back economic growth.
abstract: Commerce Dept reports wholesale inventories rose 0.3 percent in January after being flat in December; sales fell 1.3 percent, from 0.6 percent drop in December.
